Rating: 4
This was really easy and tasty! Hubs raved! I made it last night, with some modifications: whole wheat pasta (this sauce can stand up to it). I skipped the broth and used the juice from the tomatoes and red wine instead. I didn't realize until after I started cooking that the sauce was supposed to simmer for over an hour and I didn't have that kind of time, so I boiled it at full blast for about 20-25 mins instead and it was great! Next time I would cook a lower temp for recommended time as I am sure that the flavors are even more developed that way. Also, the store was out of regular havarti, so I had to buy "light" havarti, but it worked really well. Next time might take an immersion blender to the sauce--I thought it was a bit too chunky for baked pasta. Will def make again.

