This is one of my favorite dishes! It's very easy to prepare and it always gets rave reviews when we have guests. Personally, I prefer it a bit less spicy so I cut back the red pepper. Hint for pitting the olives... Lay them out on your cutting board and press with a flat object such as the bottom of a glass. Once they are squished, it's easy to pick out the stones.

