I have made this dish for my family at least one a month since the recipe was originally published in Bon Apetit in 1995. I agree with the other reviewers who think the dish makes more than four servings. I usually make the full quantity and freeze half the recipe for a later meal. I agree that substituting tomato juice for chicken stock makes a lot of sense. What I really find amazing about this recipe is that family members who normally do not tolerate spicy food seem to really love this dish. Maybe the basil (I always double the quantity)is the perfect foil for the hot pepper? Who knows why, but it works for us.

Rating: 4
I always change recipes a little bit, so here are the changes that really made the recipe an old stand-by for guests.... (1) Increase garlic to 4 cloves or more. (2) Decrease red pepper flakes by a little more than half. (3)Always use penne. I tried a smooth tube pasta and it didn't hold the sauce well and was less flavorful. (4)Substitute one can of crushed tomatoes for the other variety. I often take this dish and divide it into two casseroles...one for my family and one for friends under the weather. I always get a great response!!!!!

